      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BABY BLUE (6) goes on top. She wasn't beaten far on debut at Cranbourne over 1000m when in the market, getting back in the field and working home well to be beaten 2.75 lengths. Up in trip should suit nicely and she can improve. DREAM SUITE (7) is a filly by Ocean Park on debut for the McEvoy yard who kick her off on her home track where they're always hard to beat. She's jumped out well enough to be a strong factor. SPARKLING AWARD (4) is coming along okay, putting in a good effort at Bendigo behind a smart one last time out. She should take beating. COSMIC COMMAND (1) resumes. Two runs last time in were okay but she can be an improver this time around. MISTRESSOF MAYFAIR (9) is a filly by Churchill on debut for the Laurie yard who can run well off a jumpout win.",
